  <text>
      <front>
         <p>1888? to Harding<note xml:id="ftn3-408" place="foot" n="408">ATL MS-Copy-Micro-0485-1; Undated.</note>
         </p>
      </front>
      <body>
         <p rend="end">Friday night</p>
         <p>My Dear Sir</p>
         <p>I will thank you to write down the names &amp;c of those “<hi rend="italic">Weeklies</hi>”, you thought should have a copy of our Book sent to them:—my man shall call for it in the mg.—–</p>
         <p>I did <hi rend="italic">not</hi> visit “D.T.” (again) this mg., when in town. I was also steering for your Cove, when Hamilton hove in sight under N. &amp; Close’s verandah—&amp; so I crossed to him &amp; walked to Athenæum. I handed an advt. to D. so look out early in mg. &amp; visit E.N., &amp; in the event of your agreeing, do <hi rend="italic">you pay him</hi>, &amp; I <hi rend="italic">repay you</hi>.</p>
         <p>Yours truly, W. Colenso.</p>
      </body>
  </text>
